Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, half the @Italian Seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Parm Frico ==

While potatoes roast, lightly oil a second baking sheet. Sprinkle @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} into two 3-inch-wide circles on prepared sheet.

Bake on middle rack until cheese is golden brown and crisp, ~{6-10%minutes}.

> Check the cheese often to make sure it doesn't burn.

Let frico cool on sheet until hardened, then carefully transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

== Pesto Mayo ==

Meanwhile, using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @Portobello Mushrooms{2} ; trim any large stems if necessary. Slice @Roma Tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @Pesto{4%tbsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Portobellos ==

Drizzle both sides of each mushroom with oil; rub to evenly coat. Season all over with remaining Italian Seasoning, salt, and pepper. Arrange gill sides down on sheet used for frico.

Roast on middle rack until slightly tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

== Tomato ==

Season tomato all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add tomato and cook until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate.

== Sandwich Assembly ==

Halve and toast @Ciabatta Roll{2}; spread cut sides with half the pesto mayo. Fill ciabattas with mushrooms, tomato, and frico.

Divide sandwiches between plates along with potato wedges; sprinkle potatoes with lemon zest to taste. Serve with remaining pesto mayo and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.